  { question: "How much bigger is a 32-inch screen compared to 27-inch?", answer: "Screen area scales with the square of the diagonal. A 32-inch 16:9 screen has an area of about 437 square inches, while a 27-inch 16:9 screen has about 311 square inches. That means a 32-inch screen is about 40% larger in area than a 27-inch, despite being only 19% larger diagonally." }
